26. It is normal to certify conformance to a primary specification. The following statements should be 
used. 

"It is certified that the samples have been tested using the Test Methods stated and that the Batch 
represented by the samples conforms with DEF STAN 91-091 Issue 10 and AFQRJOS Checklist Issue 
30". 
Or 
"It is certified that the samples have been tested using the Test Methods stated and that the Batch 
represented by the samples conforms with ASTM D1655 and AFQRJOS Checklist Issue 30". 
The minimum requirements of information to be included on the fuel's refinery batch certificate of 
quality shall be: 
# Specification name, issue and any amendment number; 
# Name, telephone number, fax number, email address and postal address of testing laboratory; 
# Tank Number; 
# Batch number or unique identifier; 
# Quantity of fuel in the batch; 
# Properties tested and including specification limit, test method and result of test; 
# Additives, including qualification reference and quantity added; 
# Name and position of authorised test certificate signatory or an electronic signature; 
# Date of certification.
